The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Loose Change
                                                                                                                 LOOSE CHANGE
                              
	 UTI Master Equity Plan Unit Scheme has declared a tax-free dividend of 15 per cent (Rs 1.50 per unit on face value of Rs 10). After the payment of the dividend, the net asset value (NAV) of the scheme will fall to the extent of payout and statutory levy, if any. The record date for the dividend is April 6. The NAV per unit as on March 31 was Rs 29.39. The scheme has declared dividends at regular intervals since its launch in 2003.                            
	 Fidelity Mutual Fund has announced a second dividend of Rs. 0.70 per unit (face value of Rs 10 per unit) in its open-ended gilt scheme  Fidelity Flexi Gilt Fund  subject to availability of distributable surplus. All investors registered in the dividend option as on March 25, 2009, will be entitled to this dividend which will be tax-free in the hands of the investors.                             
	 Bharti AXA General Insurance Company Ltd has received regulatory approval for its SmartHealth Insurance policy. The policy will cover hospitalisation expenses to treat diseases and injuries as well as other value- added benefits. A separate additional sum insured will be automatically available in the case of diagnosis of any of the covered critical illnesses.                                                                                                                               
